1 SENATE FLOOR VERSION
February 9, 2026
2
3 SENATE BILL NO. 2138 By: Murdock of the Senate
4 and
5 Newton of the House
6
7
8 An Act relating to forest fire prevention; amending 2
O.S. 2021, Section 16-28.3, which relates to the
9 Oklahoma Controlled Burn Indemnity Fund; modifying
fund name; prohibiting certain reimbursement;
10 requiring creation of a prescribed burn plan for
certain landowners; requiring inclusion of certain
11 information in prescribed burn plan; requiring notice
of scheduled burn plans to landowners and local fire
12 departments; modifying plan filing fee; providing
limitation on certain reimbursement; defining term;
13 updating statutory language; and providing an
effective date.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 2 O.S. 2021, Section 16-28.3, is
18 amended to read as follows:
19 Section 16-28.3. A. There is hereby created within the
20 Oklahoma Conservation Commission, the “Oklahoma Controlled
21 Prescribed Burn Indemnity Fund”.
22 B. The Oklahoma Conservation Commission shall administer the
23 Oklahoma Controlled Prescribed Burn Indemnity Fund. The Indemnity
24 Fund shall be established for the benefit of landowners who perform
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB2138 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 cont rolled prescribed burns. The Indemnity Fund shall compensate
2 landowners for losses incurred from a prescribed fire that spreads
3 beyond the control of the burner, except for losses covered by
4 insurance. The fund shall not reimburse the participating landowner
5 for damages incurred on his or her own property.
6 C. In order to participate in the Indemnity Fund, the landowner
7 shall:
8 1. Work with the local conservation district office and the
9 Natural Resources Conservation Service of the United States
10 Department of Agriculture to develop a controlled burn plan based on
11 the United States Department of Agriculture Natural Resources
12 Conservation Service guidelines; and Have a written prescribed burn
13 plan for the parcel of land to be covered by the Indemnity Fund
14 prepared by either the local conservation district office, the
15 Natural Resources Conservation Service of the United States
16 Department of Agriculture, the Department of Wildlife Conservation,
17 Oklahoma State University Cooperative Extension Service, or other
18 recognized entity that works with landowners to develop prescribed
19 burn plans or a prescribed burn plan developed and written by the
20 landowner of the property to be burned;
21 2. Include in all burn plans submitted to the Commission for
22 coverage by the Indemnity Fund, at a minimum, the following
23 information:
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB2138 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 a. the name and telephone number of the landowner, group,
2 or organization conducting the burn,
3 b. the address and legal description of the area to be
4 burned,
5 c. the objective and purpose of the burn,
6 d. a list of all fire departments or sheriffs’ offices
7 that are required to be notified pursuant to paragraph
8 5 of this subsection,
9 e. a list of adjoining landowners required to be notified
10 pursuant to paragraph 3 of this subsection,
11 f. a description of any firebreaks used to define the
12 boundary of the prescribed burn,
13 g. a statement of prescribed weather conditions,
14 h. a description of any smoke-management considerations,
15 i. a plan for adequate manpower and firefighting
16 equipment for the control of the fire and a plan
17 providing for adequate personnel to watch over the
18 fire until it is extinguished, and
19 j. an ignition plan for the burn;
20 3. Notify, in writing or orally, all landowners whose lands
21 adjoin the owner’s land to be burned at least sixty (60) days prior
22 to conducting the burn. Such notice shall include the proposed date
23 and location of the burn and a telephone number where the owner can
24 be reached for information regarding the prescribed burn. If any
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB2138 SFLR Page 3
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 land owner is burning on a large, consolidated tract of land for
2 which there are multiple adjacent owners, only those owners with
3 adjoining land within one (1) mile of the proposed burn area shall
4 be notified;
5 4. File with the Commission at least thirty (30) days prior to
6 conducting the burn a copy of the prescribed burn plan provided for
7 in this subsection;
8 5. Notify, in writing or orally, within forty-eight (48) hours
9 of conducting the burn, the local fire departments whose response
10 area covers the land to be burned, the local county sheriff’s office
11 and, if the burn is to be conducted in a forestry service protection
12 area, a representative of the forestry service. Such notification
13 shall include the proposed date and location of the burn and a
14 telephone number where the owner can be reached for information
15 regarding the prescribed burn; and
16 2. 6. At the time of filing the completed plan, provide payment
17 of One Hundred Dollars ($100.00) Two Hundred Fifty Dollars ($250.00)
18 to the Conservation Commission.
19 D. The Conservation Commission shall have authority to invest
20 the assessments. All proceeds of the investment shall be placed in
21 the Indemnity Fund. Fifty Thousand Dollars ($50,000.00) from the
22 interest income for each year on the total proceeds in the Indemnity
23 Fund shall be paid to the Conservation Commission annually for the
24 development of controlled prescribed burn plans and for
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB2138 SFLR Page 4
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 admi nistration of the Indemnity Fund. The balance of the accrued
2 interest each year shall remain a part of the Indemnity Fund.
3 E. The maximum amount the Indemnity Fund shall pay for losses
4 arising from any one prescribed fire event is One Million Dollars
5 ($1,000,000.00). For purposes of this subsection, “losses arising
6 from any one prescribed fire event” means all activities conducted
7 pursuant to any one prescribed burn plan and, if required, burn
8 permit.
9 F. When a loss is incurred, the landowner shall present a claim
10 to the Conservation Commission. To verify the claim, the landowner
11 shall present any evidence required by the Conservation Commission
12 including, but not limited to, evidence that the landowner strictly
13 adhered to the plan provided for in subsection C of this section.
14 All landowner claim payments shall be made by the Conservation
15 Commission from the Indemnity Fund as soon as practicable and not
16 later than one (1) year following the date of claim. The price per
17 acre of land shall be established on the day of the loss and shall
18 be for the full market value on that day.
19 F. G. If there is an insufficient amount of funds in the
20 Indemnity Fund to cover all claims for a certain year, payments
21 shall be made on a pro rata basis up to one hundred percent (100%)
22 of the total loss of each landowner. If payment is not received in
23 the amount of one hundred percent (100%) of total loss for a certain
24 year, then additional amounts shall be paid as funds become
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB2138 SFLR Page 5
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 avai lable in succeeding years until repayment of one hundred percent
2 (100%) of total loss is attained. If, at any time, a landowner
3 receives payment totaling more than one hundred percent (100%) of
4 total loss, the excess payment shall be returned to the Indemnity
5 Fund within thirty (30) days. Upon final payment of a claim to a
6 landowner from the Indemnity Fund, the landowner shall subrogate the
7 interest to the Conservation Commission in a cause of action against
8 any and all parties, to the amount of loss that the producer was
9 reimbursed by the Indemnity Fund.
10 G. H. The landowner shall, within sixty (60) days of the date
11 of loss, present the claim to the Conservation Commission.
12 Landowners may submit a written request to the Conservation
13 Commission for a sixty-day extension of the filing period, if the
14 landowner can show that the landowner was not provided notification
15 and reasonable time to file a claim. If the claim of loss is not
16 presented within the time and in the manner required, the claim
17 shall be forever barred and the landowner shall forfeit all rights
18 to remuneration or payment.
19 H. I. If state funds are appropriated to the Indemnity Fund,
20 the Conservation Commission shall establish the rules and procedures
21 necessary to ensure that the General Revenue Fund shall be
22 reimbursed from the assessments in an amount equal to the total
23 appropriation made to the Indemnity Fund. The reimbursement shall
24 be made in a timely manner, provided the intents and purposes of
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB2138 SFLR Page 6
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 this section to compensate landowners for losses incurred shall not
2 be adversely affected.
3 I. J. The monies deposited in the Indemnity Fund shall at no
4 time become part of the general budget of any state board,
5 commission, or agency, except the Conservation Commission.
6 J. K. The Executive Director of the Conservation Commission
7 shall investigate all potential civil action claims against persons
8 for recovery of any losses paid by the Indemnity Fund.
9 K. L. No provision of this section shall preclude any landowner
10 from conducting a lawful burn without participating in the Oklahoma
11 Controlled Prescribed Burn Indemnity Fund.
12 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
13 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON AGRICULTURE AND WILDLIFE
